I"1<h2 id="tail--f">tail -f</h2>

<p>Example:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>tail -f /var/log/syslog
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>From man tail</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>-f, --follow[={name|descriptor}]
        output appended data as the file grows;
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Seen in <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NsK7OPlK94U">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NsK7OPlK94U</a>.</p>

<h2 id="truncate">truncate</h2>

<p>if file.txt is</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>a
b
c
d
e
f
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>then after</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>truncate -s 6 file.txt
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>it will be</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>a
b
c
</code></pre></div></div>
:ET